EMPLOYEE RETENTION
Key features of the datasets
Total Employees : Employees in the company based on gender
High Attrition Rates in Certain Roles/Departments
Overall Attrition Rate: Percentage of employees who have left the organization.
Income vs. Attrition Rate: How does monthly income impact attrition 
Attrition rate based on Job role
Gender Pay Analysis
![image](https://github.com/Mkesoju/Employee_retention/blob/main/HR%20ANALYICS%20PNG.png)

Observation: Departments like R&D might have high average working years and high attrition rates.

Long-tenured employees leaving indicates potential burnout, lack of engagement, or dissatisfaction with growth opportunities.
Departments with lower working years and high attrition may suffer from poor onboarding or lack of role clarity.

